args: C'mon, Alfonse! Time for some sparrin'!
I will be happy to serve as your opponent.
Then let's do this thing. Begin!
Whoa, these folks are fired UP!
They sure are. I'll have to join in later.
We have a winner! Alfonse takes it!
Serves me right for bein' careless.
A moment's carelessness can\ncost your life on the battlefield.
Mind if I join in, guys?
Not at all. I was hoping for a chance\nto cross swords with you.
Alfonse is top of the ranks right now,\nso knock him down a peg or three,\n{player_name}!

A battle between princes? Now THIS is
excitin' stuff! ...Oh, and no pressure, but 
the good name of our entire world is on
the line here, {player_name}.
If you raise the stakes that high, Ranzal,\nwe'll be too tense to fight.
I agree. I think we should leave both our\ncountries and social standing aside in\nthis match and simply focus on—
Prince Marth has been looking for you.\nHe found an old text that might aid\nour search.
Excellent! I will be there at once.\n...I'm sorry, Prince, but our battle will\nhave to wait until another time.
Sounds like they may have a clue\nabout how to get home.
I keep forgettin' they'll go back\nto their own world one day.
No need to make it sound like a bad thing\nwhen it's what they want, yeah?
Yeah, I know. But now that we're friends,\nit's gonna be hard to say good-bye.
I know what you mean. But AS friends,\nwe need to wish for their happiness\nand not just think of our own.
We have to believe we'll still be close\neven when we're apart.
Ah, I thought I sensed someone,\nbut I didn't know it was you, Alfonse.
My apologies for the intrusion. However,\nit's good to see you paying more attention\nto your surroundings now.
Heh. You taught me the error of my ways.\nAnyway, what brings you here?
I was hoping to find you training.
We never got a chance to finish\nthe match we started earlier.

I'm not sure either of us would have been
truly comfortable going all-out in front of
the others given our positions, but now
that we're alone, we need not hold back.
So let's fight—and do so as friends.

I could say the same. In fact, I was so
focused on your flawless technique that
I almost lost my edge. Perhaps we should
stop here for the nonce, however.
...Goodness, look at the stars.\nThey're so beautiful.
What's the night sky like in your world?
The positions of the stars are different,\nbut they radiate the same beauty.
It just makes me want to return home\nall the more.
Although it saddens me that we won't\nsee each other again after that.
I've prepared myself mentally for it,\nbut it's still unfortunate.
It depends on the structure of the gate,\nbut the idea isn't an impossibility.
Who knows? We may even find ourselves\nable to travel between our worlds freely.
You mean we could visit Askr?\nI'd love that.
If it happens, I will be happy to show you\naround and introduce you to my sister.
I really hope I can do that some day.
But even if we can't meet again,\nwe're friends now.
You know it!\nAnd no one can take that from us.
Parting will be sad, of course, but I will\nalways treasure our time together.
Thank you for blessing me with a bond\nI can believe in so strongly, my friend.
Even after you return home and start\nfighting for something else...
I know we'll continue to be friends.
